arge-scale pattern is seen in the Faraday rotation data. Diffuse polarized\nradio emission in the outer disks and halos is an excellent tracer of galaxy\ninteractions and ram pressure by the intergalactic medium. -- Intracluster gas\ncan also be significantly magnetized and highly polarized due to shocks or\ncluster mergers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Oct 2008 14:14:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Nov 2008 14:45:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 7 Jan 2009 10:06:20 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 12 Jan 2009 11:00:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
